headline: 1 Terrible Reason to Buy Ford Stock
summary: President Trump's recent rollout of tariffs has caused chaos in the stock market and plenty of uncertainty among business leaders who are trying to map out the long-term strategy for their companies.  Both Ford's (NYSE: F) and General Motors' stocks popped on that comment, with Ford's share price rising about 4% the same day Trump made his comments.  One reason why it's not a good idea to buy Ford or other auto stocks based on one comment is that President Trump could simply change his mind.

headline: This Week In Electric Vehicles - Voltera Expands Charging Infrastructure in Key Urban Markets
summary: Voltera has announced the expansion of its electric vehicle (EV) charging infrastructure in major urban markets across California, Texas, Arizona, and Florida, adding 294 charging stalls and over 28 megawatts of capacity. This expansion includes new facilities in Santa Monica, San Francisco, Dallas, and Austin, with additional sites planned for Houston, Phoenix, and Miami.
